{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Part year NI contributions should be combined to make a full year.",
        "additional_details": "It is quite possible for individuals to have a high number of incomplete qualifying years, especially where someone has worked part time or been economically inactive, but none of this would currently count towards qualification for a full state pension.\r\n\r\nAs the minimum number of qualifying years to receive a full state pension is now 35 years, the current law contributes to keeping people in poverty in retirement. This law therefore needs to be changed.",
        "background": "Part year NI contributions do not count as a qualifying year.  This discriminates against those who do not have a continuous record of being in paid employment.  In particular, this is likely to indirectly affect women.",
